<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Inline-block elements in normal flow with auto width shrink-to-fit</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html#inlineblock-width" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="Verify inline-block element with auto width shrinks-to-fit properly." />
        <style type="text/css">
            body
            {
                margin: 0;
                padding: 0;
            }
            span
            {
                display: inline-block;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if each of the words is seperated by a single space.</p>
        <div>
            Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text
            <span>Filler Text</span>
            Filler Text Filler Text Filler Text
        </div>
    </body>
</html>